{{multiple issues| {{expand Russian|date=September 2014}} {{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}} }} [[File:Artel of Artists.jpg|thumb|300px|'''Artel of Artists''' (1863-1864) (l-r) Venig, Zhuravlev, Morozov, Lemokh, Kramskoi, Litovchenko, Makovsky, Dmitriev-Orenburgsky, Petrov, Kreitan, Peskov, Shustov, Korzukhin, Grigoryev]] '''Artel of Artists''' ({{Lang-ru|«Арте́ль худо́жников»}}) was a [[cooperative]] association (''[[artel]]'') and a [[commune (intentional community)|commune]] of democratically-minded artists headed by [[Ivan Kramskoi]]. It was established in 1863 after some of its future organisers had been expelled from the [[Imperial Academy of Arts|St.&nbsp;Petersburg Academy of Arts]] because of the "revolt of fourteen". In rebellion against the Academy's annual competition, the students refused to paint an exam picture on the given topic.
A number of members of the Artel later became ''[[Peredvizhniki|Peredvizhniks]]''.
== Members == {{colbegin}} * [[Nikolai Dmitriev-Orenburgsky]] * [[Alexander Konstantinovich Grigoryev]] * [[Alexei Korzukhin]] * [[Ivan Kramskoi]] * [[Vasily Kreitan]] * [[Kirill Lemokh]] * [[Alexander Litovchenko]] * [[Konstantin Makovsky]] * [[Alexander Ivanovich Morozov]] * [[Mikhail Peskov]] * [[Nikolai Petrovich Petrov]] * [[Nikolay Shustov]] * [[Bogdan Venig]] * [[Firs Zhuravlev]] {{colend}}
