The ''' British Columbia Arts Council''' (or '''BC  Arts Council''')  is a statutory independent agency supporting arts in British Columbia.  The Council was created by the [[BC Arts Council Act, 1995]].  In the year ending March 31, 2018 Council distributed over C$24 million, in the form of awards, grants and scholarships to individuals and organizations in 225 communities across BC. <ref>http://www.bcartscouncil.ca/about/funding.htm</ref>

